I liked the puzzle. To me its an easy one. Here is my code.

w = int(input())
l = int(input())
g = []

for i in range(l):
    g += [input()]

ans = 0

for i in range(l):
    for j in range(w):
        if g[i][j]!=' ':
            if i-1>=0 and j+1<w:
                if g[i-1][j]!=' ' and g[i][j+1]!=' ': ans+=1

            if i-1>=0 and j-1>=0:
                if g[i-1][j]!=' ' and g[i][j-1]!=' ': ans+=1

            if i+1<l and j+1<w:
                if g[i+1][j]!=' ' and g[i][j+1]!=' ': ans+=1

            if i+1<l and j-1>=0:
                if g[i+1][j]!=' ' and g[i][j-1]!=' ': ans+=1

print(ans)

However I have the following suggestion?
Can we provide input ignoring blank spaces around outside of the wall? IMO it does not add any value to the problem.
